 Core components (classes, functions, and their purposes)

- Transaction (models.Transaction)
  - Represents a single financial entry with id, date, type (Income/Expense), category, description, and amount.
- BudgetModel (models.BudgetModel)
  - In-memory model holding transactions, categories, savings goal; supports add/edit/delete, totals and summaries.
- ExcelStorage (storage.ExcelStorage)
  - Loads and saves the model to an Excel workbook (.xlsx) using openpyxl, creating a structured file with sheets: Transactions, Categories, Settings.
- format_currency, parse_float, parse_date, date_to_str (utils)
  - Utility functions for formatting and parsing amounts and dates.
- BudgetApp (ui.BudgetApp)
  - Tkinter-based GUI: transaction form, table, filters, summary panel, savings goal progress, and persistence hooks.
- main (main.py)
  - Application entry point: initializes storage, model, and launches GUI.

